Use a `final` field.

Putting `final` on a field tells any developer reading your code that the class is immutable - which is good.

However, having a mutable field (private setter or not) suggests it&#39;s OK to change the value as long as the instance itself changes it. ie some other programmer may come along and add a mutating method ,like `clear()` below:

